genresAdvancedInfo.name: musica indigena mexicana
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre of music is deeply rooted in the pre-Hispanic cultures of Mexico, featuring traditional instruments such as the ocarina and the huehuetl drum. It often incorporates indigenous languages and themes of nature and spirituality, and is an important part of preserving and celebrating Mexico's indigenous heritage.
